  "local_port": 50542,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why do I see numbers and not contacts' names? In WhatsApp?",
  "response": "If you're seeing phone numbers instead of your contacts' names in WhatsApp, there are a few possible reasons for this:\n\n### 1. **Contacts Not Saved in Your Phone**\n   - WhatsApp pulls contact names from your phone's address book. If the numbers are not saved in your phone, WhatsApp will display them as they are.\n   - **Solution:** Save the numbers in your phone's contacts with the desired names. After saving, restart WhatsApp, and the names should appear.\n\n### 2. **Incorrect Country Code or Format**\n   - If the phone number in WhatsApp does not match the saved number in your contacts (e.g., missing or incorrect country code), WhatsApp won't recognize it.\n   - **Solution:** Ensure the numbers in your contacts include the correct country code and match the format used in WhatsApp.\n\n### 3. **Permissions Denied**\n   - WhatsApp needs permission to access your contacts to display names. If this permission is denied, it will only show numbers.\n   - **Solution:** Go to your phone's **Settings > Apps > WhatsApp > Permissions** and ensure \"Contacts\" is enabled.\n\n### 4. **Syncing Issues**\n   - Sometimes, contact syncing between your phone and WhatsApp may not work properly.\n   - **Solution:** Restart your phone or manually refresh your contacts in WhatsApp by going to the **Chats tab > More options (three dots) > Refresh**.\n\n### 5. **Corrupted App Data**\n   - If WhatsApp's app data is corrupt, it may not display contact names correctly.\n   - **Solution:** Clear WhatsApp's cache (go to **Settings > Apps > WhatsApp > Storage > Clear Cache**). If the issue persists, try reinstalling the app (after backing up your chats).\n\n### 6. **Multiple WhatsApp Accounts**\n   - If you're using a dual-SIM device or multiple WhatsApp accounts, the app might not recognize contacts saved under a different account.\n   - **Solution:** Ensure the contacts are saved under the SIM or account associated with the WhatsApp installation.\n\nIf none of these solutions work, there might be a deeper issue with your phone or WhatsApp. In such cases, contacting WhatsApp support should help resolve the problem.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
